I’ve replaced the complex `decodeString` implementation—which used `CharsetDecoder`, `CharBuffer`, and multiple copies—with a simple byte-array copy followed by `new String(bytes, charset)`. This leverages JVM optimizations and eliminates unnecessary memory operations.

